  "text": "the study site is subject to a considerable propagule pressure from the adjacent open areas. In fact, the study site is an old growth forest embedded in an urban landscape, with high frequency of cultivated fields and gardens. In this context, our findings suggest that natural forests at the urban interface are particularly vulnerable to invasion by non-native plants, because suburban gardens and agricultural activity can act as significant sources of plant propagules [CITATION_1] .",
